##  When to Use peerDependencies?

- When you create a library/package, you use some common packages ‚Äî like react, angular, or rxjs.
But you don‚Äôt want to install them again. You want the main app to give them.

So you say:
> ‚ÄúI need react, but the user must install it. I will only use it.‚Äù

That‚Äôs what peerDependencies means.

